NAME
  find - find indices of  boolean vector or matrix true elements

CALLING SEQUENCE
  [ii]=find(x)
  [ir,ic]=find(x)

PARAMETERS

  x    : a boolean vector or a boolean matrix

  ii, ir, ic
       : integer vectors of indices or empty matrices

DESCRIPTION
  If x is a boolean matrix,

  ii=find(x) returns the vector of indices i for which x(i) is "true". If no
  true element found find returns an empty matrix.

  [ir,ic]=find(x) returns two vectors of indices ir (for rows) and ic (for
  columns) such that x(il(n),ic(n)) is "true". If no true element found find
  returns  empty matrices in ir and ic.

EXAMPLE
  A=rand(1,20);
  w=find(A<0.5);
  A(w)
  returns the vector made of entries of A which are  < 0.5
  w=find(A>100);

